HEADWORD: Subjunction
<hw>Sub*junc"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Subjunctive</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Act of subjoining, or
state of being subjoined.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Something subjoined; <as>as, a <ex>subjunction</ex>
to a sentence</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subjunctive</ent>⟦br⟧
